           <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#ME">
                <p>Cottia Euphrosyne set this (statue) up out of her own money for Cerrinia Cottia, daughter of Lucius, a very dutiful daughter, in the place determined by the decuriones. She distributed denarii in return for the dedication of these (statues).</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p><!--commented out pending revision-->
                    <!--Rectangular base with mouldings esp. at top (all round). Finely cut letters. Dedication for ?multiple [earum] statues, offered by mother to daughter - Cerrina L. f. Cottia  by Cottia Euphrosyne. S.P.P.L.D.D.D. formula. Good photo in IMusMess, p. 102.--></p>
            </div>
